===Etymology===
From the {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|punisceement}}, {{m|fro|punisement}}, {{m|fro|punishement}}, {{m|fro|punissement}}, {{m|fro|punisshement}} and the {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|punissement}}, from the {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|pugnissement}}, from {{term||puniss-|lang=fro}} (the long stem (see the {{etyl|fr|-}} {{m|fr|-iss-}}) of {{term|punir|lang=fr||to punish}}) + {{m|fr|-ment}} (see the {{etyl|en|-}} {{m|en|-ment}}). Compare the {{etyl|en|-}} nouns {{m|en|punishing}} and {{m|en|punition}}.

